# Compose Key Configuration
#
# The compose key allows you to type special characters using key sequences.
# For example, with Menu key as compose: Menu, -, -, - produces an em-dash (—)
#
# The compose key is set via the `scripts/set-compose-key.sh` script which
# is executed on startup and reload.
#
# To change the compose key:
# 1. Set the environment variable `DOTSWAY_COMPOSE_KEY` (e.g. in .zshrc or .bashrc)
#    Example: export DOTSWAY_COMPOSE_KEY="compose:ralt"
#
# 2. Alternatively, edit the `set $compose_key` line in the main config file
#    (this will act as a fallback if the environment variable is not set).
#
# Common options:
#   compose:menu  — Menu key (default)
#   compose:ralt  — Right Alt
#   compose:lwin  — Left Windows key
#   compose:rwin  — Right Windows key
#   compose:caps  — Caps Lock
#
# See `man 7 xkeyboard-config` for more XKB options.
